"The situation where travellers or restaurant users find themselves privy to credit card details, business plans and other data is a fairly common experience. You might, for example, simply hear someone giving out their credit card details over a cellphone. There have been a number of presentations given on this phenomenon, and on every occasion at least one member of the audience offers a further example. The initial reason for embarking on research into this issue was to try to understand why this leakage occurs – or, as many people commonly think, ‘why people are so stupid’."
